must use 
#include <ncurses.h>

gcc file.c -lncurses
gcc file.c -o program -lncurses

	
initscr();

initializes terminal in curses mode
has to be called before any screen manipulation


printw();

analogous to printf but prints onto stdscr at coordinates (x, y)


refresh();

dumps contents of stdscr onto the screen
basically renders whatever you changed 

endwin();

end the curses mode
